  "slug": "cushings-disease",
  "category": "Endocrine",
  "description": "Cushing's disease results from excess cortisol, most commonly from a pituitary adenoma (PDH) or, less often, an adrenal tumour (AT). The chronic cortisol excess causes characteristic physical and metabolic changes.",
  "symptoms": [
    "Pot-bellied appearance",
    "Increased thirst and urination",
    "Increased appetite",
    "Bilateral hair loss",
    "Thin skin with bruising",
    "Lethargy"
  ],
  "severity": "medium",
  "treatment_overview": "PDH is treated medically with trilostane or mitotane, requiring regular monitoring. Adrenal tumours may be surgically removed. Treatment is lifelong and significantly improves quality of life.",
